name: Moratorium to end the War in Vietnam (1969)
description: The Moratorium to End the War in Vietnam was a massive demonstration and teach-in across the United States against the United States involvement in the Vietnam War. It took place on October 15, 1969, followed a month later, on November 15, 1969, by a large Moratorium March in Washington, D.C. This is a photo taken by Chip Walker depicting a scene during the Vietnam Moratorium Campaign.
